  "text": "The diagnostic tests available for detection of C. difficile in humans can broadly be classified into three categories [CITATION_1] . First, there are tests such as toxigenic culture to isolate toxin-producing C. difficile; second, tests that detect C. difficile products such as glutamate dehydrogenase (GDH) and toxins A and/or B; and last, tests that detects C. difficile genes.",
